						               													<description>This picture book and game tells the story of Havoc Wuzhuang Temple. The master and disciples came to Wuzhuang Temple. The disciples stole and ate the ginseng fruit and were detained by Zhenyuan Immortal. Monkey King had to seek help from all over the world, and finally invited Guanyin Bodhisattava to save the ginseng fruit tree.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Different adventure levels combined mathematical knowledge into the game to help children enlighten thinking, master knowledge, develop good habits of independent learning and active thinking. 6 games correspond to 6 education points: Understand the use of multiplication table; Recognize area; Understand the division; Observe the crystallization phenomenon. It also includes the logical ability training activity and logical reasoning training activity.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To win 6 levels of the game:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Steal Ginseng Fruit: Infer the numbers in the grid and get 8 different numbers, mark the numbers with color to show the Ginseng Fruit image&amp;#10;     Eat the Manfruit: Complete the puzzle, take out the manfruit cubes one by one, and restore the puzzle to a rectangle for 3 times&amp;#10;     Cover up and trick Taoist: Based on the information on the card, infer who told the truth and who lied, then infer who ate the ginseng fruit and who hide the manfruit &amp;#10;     Fight with Immortal Zhenyuan in the Mountain&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#154;Flip the pieces and beat your opponent, the player with more pieces on the board wins&amp;#10;     Get the Magic Water to Save the Immortal Tree: Complete the tree puzzle, mix the powder and water, pour the solution onto the tree and observe the crystallization phenomenon&amp;#10;     Immortals Gather and Taste the Fruit: Tuck the required number of rubber bands on the card to ensure the ginseng fruits can be evenly divided as required. The first one finishes 3 cards wins the game. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After player complete each level, insert the manual card to the corresponding page in the passport comes with the game. The first one who collects all 6 manual cards and fills the passport is the winner of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
